race.comment: PONTE ARCOBALENO (3) made it four minor placings in a row this preparation when narrowly beaten over 1300m at Bendigo. Threatened at this track prior, and he maps well today. Deserves another chance. MANDRAKI (12) brings two distant placings from the provincials and fourth up will be tough to beat at country level. Speed bred and he's in a leading metro stable. Has a wide gate to manage, but Coffey is a positive jockey booking.  I AM TITAN (1) resumes and has switched from the Ciaron Maher stable. He's jumped out well for the new yard stable and, notwithstanding the awkward gate, deserves consideration. HELTER PELTZER (11) debuts and won his latest jumpout. Yendall is a positive jockey engagement and he should get every opportunity.
